result.name: Shoreditch

reviews.text:
Good beer options too - Quirky British style bistro. Serviceable food as Miss Brodie would say, kale salad a cut above the mediocre whitebait. Cool vibe @ lunch.
I'd go again as an alternative to great local food. Good beer options too - old speckled hen.

Nice place. Food was good. Next to road but not too noisy. Friendly staff. I had the dinner set which was great tasting and well priced. The steak was cooked very blue when I requested rare (only reason it isn't a 5*) but I still enjoy blue anyway, so still really enjoyed it. I would recommend this as somewhere to stop by in Kennedy Town.
Nice environment and appetizers. But the mains tasted very mediocre. Some staff looked pretty green and even gave us the wrong bill...

Was excited to go - was hoping that this could be a good British pub.  It wasn’t.  Only two beers on tap.  The menu read well but the food was okay.  My impossible burger was bland - could have done with more tasty either like a sweet onion chutney or some spice.  The tomato salad was okay but the yoghurt didn’t add much - would have been better not being there or replaced by a creamy cheese like ricotta.  Finally, they didn’t take AMEX - which for the price and location seems unreasonable.

Excellent steaks, very beefy and juicy. Fish and chips are great too, crispy skin and silky flesh. I love their minty mushy peas. 
Their #haggis croquette balls are must-try too.😋😋😋
